5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 634, L.D. 974, “Resolve, to Increase the
10 High School Graduation Rate by Creating the Maine Promise Initiative”
11 Amend the resolve by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'Resolve, Directing the Department of Education to Convene a Stakeholder Group to
13 Improve High School Graduation Rates and Review Policies Related to Graduation
14 Rate Data'
15 Amend the resolve by striking out everything after the title and inserting the following:
16 'Sec. 1. Definition and policy updates; plan. Resolved: That the Department
17 of Education shall develop a plan to implement certain recommendations outlined in the
18 2025 report on high school graduation rates published by the Maine Education Policy
19 Research Institute, including, but not limited to, updating demographic definitions and data
20 suppression policies related to high school graduation rates in the State.
21 Sec. 2. Stakeholder group. Resolved: That the Department of Education shall
22 convene a stakeholder group to participate in 2 meetings. The stakeholder group shall
23 review current strategies in the Department of Education to improve high school graduation
24 rates and develop actionable graduation rate interventions based on the 2025 report on high
25 school graduation rates published by the Maine Education Policy Research Institute. The
26 department shall, by January 15, 2026, submit a report summarizing the stakeholder group's
27 discussions and the plan developed pursuant to section 1 to the Joint Standing Committee
28 on Education and Cultural Affairs. The joint standing committee may report out a bill to
29 the Second Regular Session of the 132nd Legislature.'
30 Amend the resolve by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
31 section number to read consecutively.
32 SUMMARY
3333 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, replaces the resolve
3344 and changes the title. The amendment directs the Department of Education to develop a
