315 plan to update demographic definitions and data suppression policies related to high school
326 graduation rates in the State based on the recommendations described in the 2025 report on
337 high school graduation rates published by the Maine Education Policy Research Institute.
348 The amendment also directs the department to convene a stakeholder group to review
359 current strategies within the department to improve high school graduation rates and to
460 develop actionable graduation rate interventions based on the 2025 report. The amendment
471 directs the department to submit a report based on the stakeholder group's discussions to
482 the Joint Standing Committee on Education and Cultural Affairs by January 15, 2026. The
493 committee is authorized to report out a bill to the Second Regular Session of the 132nd
1404 Legislature.
